What you need to know:

The demos in Nairobi and Kisii are a continuation of the woes the supermarket is facing. Mid this month, tens of non-unionised workers contracted to Tuskys protested what they termed as “inhumane dismissal” and failure by the ailing retailer to make a firm commitment on their severance pay.Last month, the retailer said it had signed an agreement with an undisclosed Mauritius-based fund for Sh2 billion capital injection.